WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:03.710
Dre: My son
is quite the character.

00:03.710 --> 00:07.620
He chose to go
directly into the workforce,

00:07.620 --> 00:10.620
but what he wound up doing,
you wouldn't call it a career.

00:10.620 --> 00:13.040
Yeah! What's up, guys?
Klay Thompson!

00:13.040 --> 00:14.040
[ Laughter ]

00:14.040 --> 00:15.920
[ Camera clicks ]
Alright!

00:15.920 --> 00:18.540
And with all his various jobs,

00:18.540 --> 00:21.040
he's had
varying degrees of success.

00:23.120 --> 00:24.540
♪ Here comes success ♪

00:24.540 --> 00:26.040
Hey!

00:26.040 --> 00:27.670
Stop!

00:27.670 --> 00:30.670
Through it all,
Junior's been making his way,

00:30.670 --> 00:32.750
learning the lessons
that hopefully lead

00:32.750 --> 00:35.960
to what he'll do
for the rest of his life.

00:35.960 --> 00:38.120
♪ Well, here comes my car ♪

00:38.120 --> 00:39.790
[ Indistinct talking on TV ]
Hey, guys.

00:39.790 --> 00:43.420
I figured out what I am gonna do
for the rest of my life.

00:43.420 --> 00:44.460
Okay.
Ohh!

00:44.460 --> 00:46.120
I'm getting into...

00:46.120 --> 00:47.580
comedy!

00:47.580 --> 00:49.500
Or maybe he hasn't
learned anything.

00:53.710 --> 00:56.960
♪♪

00:56.960 --> 00:58.170
Comedy?

00:59.580 --> 01:00.580
Amazing!

01:00.580 --> 01:01.920
Yup.
Mm!

01:01.920 --> 01:04.580
And I'm gonna produce a show
for unknown comics.

01:04.580 --> 01:06.710
Mm!
Unknown?

01:06.710 --> 01:08.920
Amazing!

01:08.920 --> 01:11.620
Yeah. And we're gonna be using
non-traditional venues,

01:11.620 --> 01:15.380
like empty swimming pools,
karate dojos, parking lots.

01:15.380 --> 01:17.750
And the best part is,
anyone can come.

01:17.750 --> 01:18.750
Ohh.
You hear that, Bow?

01:18.750 --> 01:19.920
Huh?
No quality control.

01:19.920 --> 01:22.380
Hmm.
Amazing!

01:22.380 --> 01:23.830
I'm putting on a show
tomorrow night,

01:23.830 --> 01:25.040
and I'd love
if you guys could come.

01:25.040 --> 01:25.790
Well --

01:25.790 --> 01:27.750
Of course! Yes!

01:27.750 --> 01:30.210
We would do anything
to support you.

01:30.210 --> 01:31.210
Thank you, guys.

01:31.210 --> 01:33.040
But make sure
that you get there early,

01:33.040 --> 01:35.620
because I hear
tickets are gonna sell out.

01:35.620 --> 01:37.170
[ Laughter ]

01:37.170 --> 01:39.250
They're not gonna sell out.
They're free. Right?

01:39.250 --> 01:41.620
[ Laughter ]

01:41.620 --> 01:43.290
Mwah.
So proud of you, sweetie.

01:43.290 --> 01:44.710
Thanks, Mom.
So proud of you, son!

01:44.710 --> 01:46.540
[ Both laugh ]

01:48.120 --> 01:49.250
What is up
with that kid?

01:49.250 --> 01:50.750
"Parking lot comedy"?

01:50.750 --> 01:52.750
It's like he's just
pulling words out of a hat!

01:52.750 --> 01:54.790
This is Migos
all over again.

01:54.790 --> 01:56.250
There's no future
in this.

01:56.250 --> 01:58.330
It ain't real.

01:58.330 --> 02:00.500
None of it's been real.

02:00.500 --> 02:03.330
But, Dre, we have to
be patient with him.

02:03.330 --> 02:05.330
Yeah, I know.

02:05.330 --> 02:06.670
But I would've
figured it out by now.

02:06.670 --> 02:08.330
[ Scoffs ]

02:08.330 --> 02:10.420
Do you know what I could have
done with us as parents?

02:10.420 --> 02:13.420
At least been a high-ranking
deacon in a mega-church.

02:13.420 --> 02:14.790
They make bank, Bow.

02:14.790 --> 02:16.920
I mean, private planes,
Chardonnay, shrimp.

02:16.920 --> 02:18.830
Junior ain't got no shrimp.
Can I get an amen?

02:18.830 --> 02:19.620
Are you done?!

02:19.620 --> 02:21.670
Uh...

02:21.670 --> 02:22.750
Yeah. I think I am.

02:22.750 --> 02:24.080
Okay.

02:24.080 --> 02:26.540
We said we would
have his back, alright?

02:26.540 --> 02:29.960
So, we are gonna go
to the comedy show.

02:29.960 --> 02:32.380
Why?
And then,

02:32.380 --> 02:34.790
we are gonna sneak out
when he's not looking.

02:34.790 --> 02:36.330
and on the way home,

02:36.330 --> 02:38.460
I'm-a get you some Chardonnay
and some shrimps.

02:38.460 --> 02:40.250
Can you also call me...

02:40.250 --> 02:41.960
"Reverend Johnson"?

02:41.960 --> 02:45.210
Will you finally call me
"Dr. Johnson"?

02:49.380 --> 02:50.920
You know I just can't
give you that.

02:50.920 --> 02:51.920
What?

02:51.920 --> 02:53.500
[ Cellphone chimes ]

02:55.120 --> 02:57.210
Look at God.

02:57.210 --> 02:59.000
Emily's slumber party
got canceled.

02:59.000 --> 03:00.500
She's saying her house
is getting fumigated,

03:00.500 --> 03:03.380
but we all know
her dad cheated on her mom.

03:03.380 --> 03:06.000
Perfect timing, Mr. Copeland,
because I did not want to go.

03:06.000 --> 03:07.580
What do you mean
you didn't want to go?

03:07.580 --> 03:10.830
Diane, sleepovers are the most
magical time in a kid's life.

03:10.830 --> 03:12.750
Um, what's magical

03:12.750 --> 03:14.750
about getting
four hours of garbage sleep

03:14.750 --> 03:15.920
on a stranger's floor?

03:15.920 --> 03:17.420
Okay.

03:17.420 --> 03:20.380
Sleepovers are
so much more than that.

03:20.380 --> 03:22.120
I loved them as a kid.

03:22.120 --> 03:24.710
Oh. I have an idea.

03:24.710 --> 03:28.710
Why don't you have
the sleepover at our house?

03:28.710 --> 03:32.580
School is where you plant
the seeds of friendships.

03:32.580 --> 03:34.580
Sleepovers --

03:34.580 --> 03:37.830
Sleepovers are where
those friendships blossom.

03:37.830 --> 03:39.620
Your future best friends
are gonna be made

03:39.620 --> 03:41.620
while you're
watching scary movies

03:41.620 --> 03:43.830
and braiding
each other's hair

03:43.830 --> 03:47.170
[ Whispering ]
and telling each other
your deepest secrets.

03:49.580 --> 03:51.250
Okay.

03:51.250 --> 03:52.710
Since it'll make you happy,
I'll do it.

03:52.710 --> 03:55.330
But only if you stop
doing that weird dance.

03:55.330 --> 03:56.330
Sorry.

03:56.330 --> 03:57.580
Okay.
[ Normal voice ]
So sorry.

03:57.580 --> 04:01.670
♪♪

04:01.670 --> 04:03.330
[ Whispering ]
Sleepover!

04:03.330 --> 04:04.830
Mom!

04:04.830 --> 04:08.580
Alright. American Express
is relaunching the Green Card.

04:08.580 --> 04:10.670
Oh, the O.G.!
[ Chuckles ]

04:10.670 --> 04:13.380
Okay, you can just say
"original."

04:13.380 --> 04:14.460
Copy that.
Alright?

04:14.460 --> 04:16.380
And if we get
their account,

04:16.380 --> 04:19.040
they want to focus
on advertising to millennials.

04:19.040 --> 04:21.420
Now, I say
we pitch them a campaign

04:21.420 --> 04:24.830
that showcases their Green Card
as a milestone for growing up.

04:24.830 --> 04:26.330
Mm.
Mm-hmm.

04:26.330 --> 04:28.750
Like, when you go from
crashing on your buddy's couch

04:28.750 --> 04:30.170
to having your own place.

04:30.170 --> 04:33.750
Ah. Like we all
have definitely done.

04:33.750 --> 04:35.120
Or when you take that step

04:35.120 --> 04:37.460
from having a job
to having a career.

04:37.460 --> 04:40.710
With the Green Card, you can
start living your life...

04:40.710 --> 04:41.880
express.

04:41.880 --> 04:43.710
Wow.
Ooh!

04:43.710 --> 04:45.120
Outstanding, Dre.

04:45.120 --> 04:47.830
That is the best idea
you've had all year.

04:47.830 --> 04:50.080
And, uh...
I'm not just saying that

04:50.080 --> 04:52.250
'cause I accidentally called you
"Charlie" yesterday.

04:52.250 --> 04:53.540
Oh, I'm not offended.

04:53.540 --> 04:56.170
Mistaken identity is how
I got into the Soho House.

04:59.540 --> 05:01.880
I've got a long history
with American Express.

05:01.880 --> 05:04.040
When I bought my fish fry truck,
American Express was there.

05:04.040 --> 05:05.830
Mm.

05:05.830 --> 05:08.460
When I couldn't pay my fish guy,
American Express was there.

05:08.460 --> 05:10.330
When the fish oil got too hot
and I hit a pothole

05:10.330 --> 05:12.710
and my truck burst into flames,
guess who was there.

05:12.710 --> 05:13.960
American Express.

05:13.960 --> 05:15.750
Nnh-nnh-nnh. Maybe.

05:15.750 --> 05:18.040
I blacked out
due to smoke inhalation.

05:18.040 --> 05:20.670
Listen,
this American Express account

05:20.670 --> 05:23.210
is very important
for Stevens & Lido --

05:23.210 --> 05:24.620
and also
to me personally,

05:24.620 --> 05:26.420
because I recently
started gambling,

05:26.420 --> 05:28.380
and it turns out,
I'm terrible at it.

05:28.380 --> 05:30.330
So let's celebrate.

05:30.330 --> 05:32.460
Martinis at the club --
on me. Come on.

05:32.460 --> 05:34.830
Hey, hey.
I can't tonight, alright?

05:34.830 --> 05:37.920
I'm being forced to support
my son's comedy show.

05:37.920 --> 05:40.120
It's his latest
career left turn.

05:40.120 --> 05:42.120
I was so much more focused
at his age.

05:42.120 --> 05:43.830
It's true, Dre.

05:43.830 --> 05:46.620
The day that you
stopped slinging rocks
on the street corner

05:46.620 --> 05:48.460
and got into the world
of advertising

05:48.460 --> 05:50.880
was the day that probably
saved your life.

05:50.880 --> 05:52.710
I never sold drugs.

05:52.710 --> 05:54.750
Is that what
"slinging rocks" meant?

05:54.750 --> 05:58.170
I thought -- I thought
"rocks" were basketballs, no?

05:58.170 --> 06:02.040
Okay, look, I don't have
high expectations for tonight.

06:02.040 --> 06:04.420
Until Junior
does something impressive,

06:04.420 --> 06:06.210
I'm just gonna go along
for the ride --

06:06.210 --> 06:08.920
you know, sip on
a low-alcoholic Mexican beer

06:08.920 --> 06:10.670
and sit back and wonder

06:10.670 --> 06:13.460
why all those comics
hate their parents.

06:13.460 --> 06:15.670
After all,
how could Junior's show

06:15.670 --> 06:17.710
be any more lame
than he'd been?

06:17.710 --> 06:18.880
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:18.880 --> 06:19.880
Wow.

06:19.880 --> 06:20.880
[ Gasps ]

06:20.880 --> 06:22.380
Wow.

06:22.380 --> 06:26.210
Junior totally transformed
this butcher shop.

06:26.210 --> 06:28.920
Oh, my God!
Look at the lights, Dre!

06:28.920 --> 06:29.960
[ Chuckles ]

06:29.960 --> 06:31.670
Look at the people!

06:31.670 --> 06:32.960
I know.

06:32.960 --> 06:34.000
Is our son impressive?

06:35.580 --> 06:37.580
Oh, Bow.

06:37.580 --> 06:38.960
You will always be

06:38.960 --> 06:41.460
that simple, simple girl
from the commune, won't you?

06:41.460 --> 06:42.460
[ Scoffs ]

06:42.460 --> 06:44.250
Those are twinkle lights,
alright?

06:44.250 --> 06:46.420
He strung up 1999
around the room.

06:46.420 --> 06:48.000
Alright, I don't get
any of this.

06:48.000 --> 06:50.170
This...is not for me.

06:50.170 --> 06:51.830
Not for you?

06:51.830 --> 06:54.040
Baby, this is you.

06:54.040 --> 06:55.460
What are you
talking about?

06:55.460 --> 06:58.750
Oh, I remember a young boy
with child-bearing hips

06:58.750 --> 07:02.290
and dreams big enough
to fill an empty warehouse.

07:02.290 --> 07:04.620
[ Up-tempo music plays ]
You came back from Howard
with the idea

07:04.620 --> 07:08.250
you could bring go-go music
from D.C. to L.A.

07:08.250 --> 07:10.750
[ Laughs ]
You couldn't.

07:10.750 --> 07:15.210
It was the worst thing to happen
to this city in 1992.

07:15.210 --> 07:17.380
[ Siren wailing ]
And, yeah, I know
what else happened that year.

07:17.380 --> 07:18.790
[ Laughs ]

07:18.790 --> 07:20.380
Dre,
you've got to see it.

07:20.380 --> 07:21.380
See what?

07:21.380 --> 07:22.960
You will always be

07:22.960 --> 07:26.710
that simple, simple boy
from Compton, Dre.

07:26.710 --> 07:27.960
[ Laughs ]

07:27.960 --> 07:29.330
Come on.
Really?

07:29.330 --> 07:31.290
Junior is following
in your footsteps.

07:31.290 --> 07:33.040
Mm-hmm.
He got into Howard.

07:33.040 --> 07:35.250
Okay.
He worked
at Stevens & Lido.

07:35.250 --> 07:39.080
And you both hate
small talk from baristas.

07:39.080 --> 07:41.380
And how is
your day going?

07:41.380 --> 07:42.670
Venti.
Venti.

07:42.670 --> 07:45.210
He's turning into you.

07:45.210 --> 07:46.750
On purpose.

07:46.750 --> 07:48.290
Was Bow right?

07:48.290 --> 07:50.920
Did my son want to be like me?

07:50.920 --> 07:54.080
Was my son just trying to
re-create his father's glory,

07:54.080 --> 07:56.000
like Jesus or something?

07:56.000 --> 07:57.210
Nice sweater.

07:57.210 --> 07:58.540
Thank you.
Oh, thank you.

07:59.920 --> 08:03.170
Great Andres
think alike, right?

08:03.170 --> 08:05.420
They do...

08:05.420 --> 08:07.120
son.

08:10.330 --> 08:12.920
My son wanted to be
just like me --

08:12.920 --> 08:14.460
and I didn't hate it.

08:14.460 --> 08:15.790
Ooh, ooh!

08:15.790 --> 08:17.000
Hello, Junior.

08:17.000 --> 08:17.750
Dad.

08:17.750 --> 08:20.380
You know, um...

08:20.380 --> 08:22.750
Son, I just wanted to say
you weren't...

08:22.750 --> 08:25.580
running away from college
when you dropped out of Howard.

08:25.580 --> 08:26.960
You...

08:26.960 --> 08:28.540
You were running...

08:28.540 --> 08:30.380
to me.

08:30.380 --> 08:31.330
I was?

08:31.330 --> 08:33.120
Yes.

08:33.120 --> 08:35.920
Think about it.
Alright?

08:35.920 --> 08:40.120
You are on a trail
that I blazed for you.

08:40.120 --> 08:43.420
Alright? You are doing exactly
what I did when I was your age.

08:43.420 --> 08:45.580
I guess I am.

08:45.580 --> 08:48.420
And maybe the reason
you've been so hard on me

08:48.420 --> 08:50.120
is because you actually
don't like yourself.

08:50.120 --> 08:52.040
Oh, no.
I love me some me.

08:52.040 --> 08:53.290
Oh, okay.
Alright?

08:53.290 --> 08:56.000
But you...

08:56.000 --> 08:58.170
you are my true heir.

08:58.170 --> 09:00.620
And it's time
for me to school you.

09:00.620 --> 09:02.880
Morgan Freeman:
The University of Dre.

09:02.880 --> 09:04.120
Integrity...

09:04.120 --> 09:05.710
perseverance...

09:05.710 --> 09:07.420
dopeness.

09:07.420 --> 09:11.380
We take boys
and turn them to men.

09:11.380 --> 09:15.170
We take men
and turn them into Dre.

09:15.170 --> 09:17.170
Do you have what it takes?

09:17.170 --> 09:18.960
University of Dre.

09:18.960 --> 09:21.380
Do you have what it takes?

09:21.380 --> 09:22.460
Yeah!
Yeah!
Yeah!
Yeah!

09:22.460 --> 09:25.620
♪♪

09:25.620 --> 09:29.080
I am committed
to doing whatever it takes

09:29.080 --> 09:31.960
to help you get
to where I am.

09:31.960 --> 09:34.120
Well, I've got another show
tomorrow night, if you're fr--

09:34.120 --> 09:35.420
Uh, shh.
...free.

09:35.420 --> 09:36.460
Shh.

09:36.460 --> 09:38.540
Don't say another word.

09:38.540 --> 09:40.540
I'm there.

09:40.540 --> 09:41.880
No.

09:41.880 --> 09:45.540
We're there.

09:45.540 --> 09:47.830
♪ Back to life ♪

09:47.830 --> 09:51.420
Dre: The next night,
we went to Junior's show.

09:51.420 --> 09:53.420
I was ready to step in

09:53.420 --> 09:56.580
and make it
the best it could be.

09:56.580 --> 09:59.250
But Junior was already
killing it.

09:59.250 --> 10:01.380
It caught me off-guard.

10:01.380 --> 10:04.880
But to these people,
he wasn't my son.

10:04.880 --> 10:07.080
He was his own man.

10:07.080 --> 10:10.540
And that man was cool as hell.

10:10.540 --> 10:12.420
What's up?

10:12.420 --> 10:15.540
You guys look cool enough
to know where the coatcheck is.

10:15.540 --> 10:17.620
Charlie,
it's me and Junior.

10:17.620 --> 10:19.580
Oh, snap!

10:19.580 --> 10:21.210
It is y'all!

10:22.500 --> 10:24.620
Where's the coatcheck,
though?

10:24.620 --> 10:25.880
Eh...

10:25.880 --> 10:28.540
Back home,
Bow and Diane were trying

10:28.540 --> 10:30.290
to make slumber party magic.

10:30.290 --> 10:32.460
Hello, ladies!

10:32.460 --> 10:34.040
Hi!

10:34.040 --> 10:36.710
I made you some cookies,
and I brought some napkins,

10:36.710 --> 10:39.830
because we are generally not
a house that eats food upstairs.

10:39.830 --> 10:43.620
But it's a special occasion,
so, you know, made an exception.

10:43.620 --> 10:44.710
[ Laughs ]

10:44.710 --> 10:45.960
Hey, Diane, can I talk
to you for a sec?

10:45.960 --> 10:47.170
Yeah.
Okay.
We'll be right back.

10:47.170 --> 10:48.170
Have fun.

10:48.170 --> 10:50.580
[ Girls talking, giggling ]

10:50.580 --> 10:52.500
How's it going?

10:52.500 --> 10:54.830
Oh. Pretty good.
Everyone dug the pizza.

10:54.830 --> 10:57.210
And it turns out Emily loves
murder podcasts, too.

10:57.210 --> 10:58.540
Ohh!
Mm-hmm.

10:58.540 --> 11:00.750
And we've been talking a lot
of smack about Jhene Irwin.

11:00.750 --> 11:02.540
[ Gasps ]
I'm so excited,

11:02.540 --> 11:05.460
'cause this is
the best night ever.

11:05.460 --> 11:07.790
Is it? Okay.
Come here.
The best night ever.

11:07.790 --> 11:10.080
Oh, God! This is so great.
Oh, my God. I'm so proud of you.

11:10.080 --> 11:11.460
Go in there. Go in there,
Go, go!

11:11.460 --> 11:13.210
Alright, guys,
Have fun.

11:13.210 --> 11:14.290
[ Laughs ]

11:14.290 --> 11:16.250
Have fun! Bye!

11:16.250 --> 11:18.460
So, you want
to crack open the Ouija board

11:18.460 --> 11:19.920
or braid some hair?

11:19.920 --> 11:21.540
Is your mom
really gone?

11:21.540 --> 11:22.620
Yeah.

11:22.620 --> 11:24.420
Good. I'm out.

11:24.420 --> 11:26.250
Wait, what?

11:26.250 --> 11:27.880
I'm sneaking out
to meet my boyfriend.

11:27.880 --> 11:30.710
His dad works for Red Bull.
He's met Rob Dyrdek.

11:30.710 --> 11:31.790
Later, losers!

11:31.790 --> 11:36.210
♪♪

11:36.210 --> 11:38.580
So...

11:38.580 --> 11:40.670
Jhene Irwin --
the worst.

11:40.670 --> 11:42.540
[ Chuckles ] Right?

11:42.540 --> 11:45.330
♪♪

11:45.330 --> 11:47.080
[ Indistinct conversations ]

11:47.080 --> 11:49.830
Hey, man. The crowd's getting
a little restless.

11:49.830 --> 11:51.210
We should do something.

11:51.210 --> 11:53.000
My opener is
stuck in traffic.

11:53.000 --> 11:55.000
Okay, well, you know...

11:55.000 --> 11:57.250
you got to do
something.

11:57.250 --> 11:59.830
Hey. You want me
to get on stage and do 10?

11:59.830 --> 12:01.040
Nah.

12:01.040 --> 12:02.120
Good.

12:02.120 --> 12:03.920
'Cause I only got five.

12:03.920 --> 12:05.620
Plus, the Shannon Sharpe
impersonation --

12:05.620 --> 12:08.790
it is...
slightly racist.

12:08.790 --> 12:10.460
Ooh! I got it.
Hmm?

12:10.460 --> 12:12.250
We'll raffle off
a free brisket

12:12.250 --> 12:14.380
for everybody who signs up
for the e-mail list.

12:14.380 --> 12:15.880
Okay. Okay.

12:15.880 --> 12:17.620
You go get the brisket,
and I'll start the e-mail list.

12:17.620 --> 12:19.580
Gotcha.
Okay.

12:19.580 --> 12:22.120
Father and son
working together.

12:22.120 --> 12:25.000
Got to say, it felt nice.

12:26.290 --> 12:27.500
[ Both chuckle ]

12:27.500 --> 12:29.040
[ Snoring ]

12:29.040 --> 12:30.500
How is she asleep?

12:30.500 --> 12:32.710
It's not even 9:00.
My grandma's wig is still on.

12:32.710 --> 12:34.500
[ Both chuckle ]

12:34.500 --> 12:36.040
You know what?
Hmm?

12:36.040 --> 12:37.500
We should prank her.

12:37.500 --> 12:39.540
[ Gasps ] Yes!

12:39.540 --> 12:41.330
We should burn her clothes
in the backyard.

12:42.540 --> 12:45.380
I was thinking we just
put her hand in water --

12:45.380 --> 12:47.120
you know, so she pees
her sleeping bag.

12:47.120 --> 12:48.920
Oh, okay. Yeah,
that's -- that's cool, too.

12:48.920 --> 12:50.000
[ Chuckles ]

12:52.040 --> 12:53.960
This is
going to be hilarious.

12:53.960 --> 12:55.250
Yeah, and in 20 years,

12:55.250 --> 12:57.500
when I text you an emoji
of a glass of water,

12:57.500 --> 12:59.080
we'll both remember
this exact moment,

12:59.080 --> 13:01.420
when we became
best friends.

13:01.420 --> 13:02.880
Oh. What are
you guys up to?

13:02.880 --> 13:04.290
Standard sleepover stuff.

13:04.290 --> 13:06.000
Going to humiliate
a classmate,

13:06.000 --> 13:07.710
sacrifice the one
for the friendship of the two.

13:07.710 --> 13:09.580
Right, Savannah?

13:09.580 --> 13:10.540
Savannah?

13:12.420 --> 13:14.290
Alright.
Well, have fun.

13:16.500 --> 13:18.420
[ Chuckles ] Oh, my gosh.
Does he live here?

13:18.420 --> 13:19.920
Yes.
He's my twin brother.

13:19.920 --> 13:21.290
That's so weird.

13:21.290 --> 13:22.380
He's so weird.

13:22.380 --> 13:23.420
Am I being weird?

13:23.420 --> 13:24.420
Yes.

13:25.790 --> 13:27.000
What are you doing?

13:27.000 --> 13:29.120
Liking all of Jack's photos
on Instagram.

13:29.120 --> 13:32.380
♪♪

13:32.380 --> 13:34.460
[ Jamaican accent ]
You understand me?

13:34.460 --> 13:35.960
That's what it's like
being Jamaican.

13:35.960 --> 13:39.420
[ Laughter ]

13:39.420 --> 13:41.080
Son, he's funny.

13:41.080 --> 13:42.540
Yeah, he's a big get.

13:42.540 --> 13:44.670
He got fired
from "SNL" and "Kimmel."

13:44.670 --> 13:46.330
Hey, Junior?

13:46.330 --> 13:48.750
I'm Jasmine Smith.
I run the Dynasty Typewriter.

13:48.750 --> 13:50.170
Yeah. I love your room.

13:50.170 --> 13:52.080
You guys put on
some of the best comedy shows.

13:52.080 --> 13:54.290
Well, we actually need
someone to run our venue
during the week,

13:54.290 --> 13:57.290
so if you're available,
we should talk.

13:57.290 --> 13:59.040
Thank you.
I'll definitely give you a call.

13:59.040 --> 14:00.170
Great.

14:02.080 --> 14:04.000
Dad, did you
just see that?

14:04.000 --> 14:05.880
We took the show
to the next level,

14:05.880 --> 14:07.710
and I got a job offer.

14:07.710 --> 14:10.380
Well, when you
put on a great show,
people take notice.

14:10.380 --> 14:11.960
If I go to work
with Dynasty Typewriter,

14:11.960 --> 14:14.250
that could open
so many doors.

14:14.250 --> 14:16.710
I'd be meeting
the best comedians,

14:16.710 --> 14:19.420
maybe take the show on the road
and find new talent

14:19.420 --> 14:21.290
and bring it
to the masses.

14:21.290 --> 14:23.670
Well...yeah.

14:23.670 --> 14:26.330
That-- That's
one possible future.

14:26.330 --> 14:27.710
No, no, no.
I think I found my thing.

14:27.710 --> 14:29.210
I-I-I got to go call Mom.

14:29.210 --> 14:33.210
My son's big night
ended in a huge opportunity.

14:33.210 --> 14:35.750
So, why did it feel like
I had been punched in the gut?

14:35.750 --> 14:37.080
[ Laughter ]

14:40.540 --> 14:42.830
Grandma, you are not
gonna believe it.

14:42.830 --> 14:45.040
I got an offer
to run Dynasty Typewriter!

14:45.040 --> 14:46.170
Ohhh!

14:46.170 --> 14:47.540
That's great, baby!

14:47.540 --> 14:48.830
[ Chuckles ]

14:48.830 --> 14:50.330
Hey. Is it great?

14:50.330 --> 14:52.290
'Cause I have no idea
what any of those words meant.

14:52.290 --> 14:54.330
It is.
I'm happy for him.

14:54.330 --> 14:56.380
Oh, really?

14:56.380 --> 14:58.290
Then why do you
sound like you did

14:58.290 --> 14:59.620
when I told you
I shot your daddy?

14:59.620 --> 15:00.960
Damn, Mama.

15:00.960 --> 15:02.170
Yeah, what's wrong?

15:02.170 --> 15:04.420
No, I am really happy
for Junior,

15:04.420 --> 15:08.040
but part of me doesn't
want him to take it.

15:08.040 --> 15:10.620
You know, I-I only just
found out he was on my path,

15:10.620 --> 15:12.620
and I'm not ready for him
to leave just yet.

15:12.620 --> 15:13.960
Mm.

15:13.960 --> 15:17.670
We had a whole thing going.
We were connecting.

15:17.670 --> 15:20.620
And maybe I'm selfish,
but...

15:20.620 --> 15:23.080
I like this new era
of Dre and Junior.

15:23.080 --> 15:25.290
Hey.

15:25.290 --> 15:27.000
But this is
Junior's life.
Yes.

15:27.000 --> 15:29.210
Now, you got to make
all of your decisions

15:29.210 --> 15:30.790
on your own, didn't you?

15:30.790 --> 15:33.750
Well, now it's his turn.

15:33.750 --> 15:36.920
He gets to choose.

15:39.000 --> 15:40.250
Okay?

15:40.250 --> 15:43.120
Now,
if you'll excuse me...

15:43.120 --> 15:46.330
I met a man
at Junior's comedy show,

15:46.330 --> 15:49.250
and we exchanged
some innuendo.

15:49.250 --> 15:50.330
[ Chuckles ]

15:50.330 --> 15:54.120
He put me in his phone
as "Lady Sausage,"

15:54.120 --> 15:55.960
so we're off
to a good start.

15:55.960 --> 15:57.960
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, yeah!

15:57.960 --> 16:00.120
[ Vocalizes "First Call" ]

16:02.000 --> 16:03.880
Mama was right.

16:03.880 --> 16:06.210
I couldn't make
Junior's choice for him,

16:06.210 --> 16:08.380
but I could give him
another option.

16:08.380 --> 16:10.750
[ Chuckles ]

16:10.750 --> 16:12.790
I haven't seen
the Pros and Cons Board

16:12.790 --> 16:15.710
since you were deciding
whether or not to grow a Mohawk.

16:15.710 --> 16:16.920
[ Chuckles ]

16:16.920 --> 16:18.710
Mr. T left a void.

16:18.710 --> 16:19.790
[ Chuckles ]

16:19.790 --> 16:21.250
You know,
this Dynasty Typewriter thing --

16:21.250 --> 16:22.460
I-I don't know.

16:22.460 --> 16:24.170
I like working
for myself,

16:24.170 --> 16:28.170
but there are a lot of reasons
to take this job.

16:28.170 --> 16:31.960
Well, I'm not gonna make
your decision any easier, son.

16:36.500 --> 16:39.250
I think you should come
work with me at Stevens & Lido.

16:39.250 --> 16:41.830
You know, we're starting
this American Express campaign

16:41.830 --> 16:43.120
geared towards millennials,

16:43.120 --> 16:46.380
and clearly, you know
exactly what they want.

16:46.380 --> 16:47.830
Really?

16:47.830 --> 16:49.500
I talked to Jasmine,

16:49.500 --> 16:52.120
and she offered me
creative control, benefits,

16:52.120 --> 16:54.330
and I'd be making
twice what I am now.

16:54.330 --> 16:55.830
Ooh.
So...

16:55.830 --> 16:57.580
We can't offer you
any of that.

16:57.580 --> 16:59.420
But we can offer you
a parking space.

16:59.420 --> 17:00.710
Ooh.

17:00.710 --> 17:03.500
On days you drive to work
with me.

17:03.500 --> 17:05.710
Dad...
where's this coming from?

17:05.710 --> 17:07.380
Well, Junior...

17:07.380 --> 17:08.960
I like working with you.

17:08.960 --> 17:11.580
I want this to keep going

17:11.580 --> 17:14.710
and take your career to
the next level at the same time.

17:16.880 --> 17:19.120
I don't know.

17:19.120 --> 17:20.670
I've got to
think about it.

17:20.670 --> 17:22.830
Okay.

17:22.830 --> 17:24.380
You think about it.

17:24.380 --> 17:26.790
You know, it's, uh...

17:26.790 --> 17:29.330
It's your choice to make.
I get it.

17:29.330 --> 17:30.830
You know, I'm just
gonna go in the house

17:30.830 --> 17:33.420
and look at
some of these, uh...

17:33.420 --> 17:35.290
old baby pictures
of you --

17:35.290 --> 17:38.080
in particular, the ones
from the day you were born.

17:39.540 --> 17:40.790
Did you know, uh,

17:40.790 --> 17:45.380
I cut your umbilical cord
with these hands?

17:45.380 --> 17:46.460
Ah.

17:46.460 --> 17:47.670
Don't worry about that.

17:47.670 --> 17:50.500
♪♪

17:50.500 --> 17:53.330
[ Car engine revving ]

17:53.330 --> 17:55.040
You're really good
at this.

17:55.040 --> 17:56.420
Thanks.

17:56.420 --> 17:58.000
I'm good at pretty much
everything I try.

17:58.000 --> 17:59.500
My mom says
I'm like an ant,

17:59.500 --> 18:01.670
'cause I can lift
more than my own body weight.

18:01.670 --> 18:02.750
Want to see me
do push-ups?

18:02.750 --> 18:04.040
Yes, please.

18:04.040 --> 18:06.920
[ Video game beeps ]

18:06.920 --> 18:07.880
[ Whispering ] Hey.

18:07.880 --> 18:09.790
How's it going?

18:09.790 --> 18:11.830
I thought you said
I was gonna make best friends.

18:11.830 --> 18:13.170
[ Normal voice ] Oh, no.

18:13.170 --> 18:14.670
But Savannah is
obsessed with Jack,

18:14.670 --> 18:16.330
[ Sighs ]
Sophie needs
a CPAP machine,

18:16.330 --> 18:18.000
and Emily's --

18:18.000 --> 18:19.540
Never mind about Emily.

18:19.540 --> 18:21.080
This whole night
has been a bust.

18:21.080 --> 18:24.750
Oh, Diane,
I'm so sorry.

18:24.750 --> 18:26.460
But the important thing is,

18:26.460 --> 18:28.670
you put yourself out there
when you didn't want to.

18:28.670 --> 18:30.830
Taking a risk
like that --

18:30.830 --> 18:31.920
oh, it'll pay off.

18:31.920 --> 18:33.710
I promise.

18:33.710 --> 18:35.420
Thanks, Mom.
You're welcome.

18:35.420 --> 18:37.210
I really do
appreciate you trying,

18:37.210 --> 18:39.040
but I think I'm just gonna
hold this L and go to bed.

18:39.040 --> 18:40.500
What? No!

18:40.500 --> 18:43.420
Sweetheart, don't lose faith
in the sleepover.

18:43.420 --> 18:45.830
These girls are duds.

18:45.830 --> 18:48.580
And we're gonna get
a whole new crop, and
we're gonna run it back!

18:48.580 --> 18:50.880
[ Chuckles ]
Sleepovers!

18:50.880 --> 18:52.210
[ Snoring ]

18:55.290 --> 18:57.170
This is
the worst sleepover ever.

18:57.170 --> 18:58.210
I've been to worse.
[ Gasps ]

18:58.210 --> 18:59.580
What?! I thought
you were asleep!

18:59.580 --> 19:02.250
I was pretending to be asleep
so I could prank everybody.

19:02.250 --> 19:04.920
Wait, you pretended
to be asleep for hours?

19:04.920 --> 19:06.500
That's totally
something I would do.

19:06.500 --> 19:07.620
Really?
Yeah.

19:07.620 --> 19:09.120
I'll lie in wait for days,
like a snake,

19:09.120 --> 19:10.330
and then I strike.

19:10.330 --> 19:11.380
[ Chuckles ]
That's so cool.

19:11.380 --> 19:12.580
Thank you.

19:12.580 --> 19:14.790
Oh, and your fake snore
is top-notch.

19:14.790 --> 19:16.120
Thanks. [ Chuckles ]
Mm-hmm.

19:16.120 --> 19:18.750
Want to go tell Savannah
that Jack still wets the bed?

19:18.750 --> 19:20.500
Yes.
Yes, I do.

19:20.500 --> 19:25.460
♪♪

19:25.460 --> 19:27.170
Hey, Dad, Dad.
Yeah?

19:27.170 --> 19:30.710
You know...
after we talked last night,

19:30.710 --> 19:33.750
I walked away knowing that my
future is with Stevens & Lido.

19:33.750 --> 19:35.290
That's great, son.

19:35.290 --> 19:38.080
But then I re-read
the e-mail from Jasmine

19:38.080 --> 19:39.540
and was reminded

19:39.540 --> 19:41.250
that I'd be getting
a percentage of the door.

19:41.250 --> 19:42.790
Oh.
So I went to bed

19:42.790 --> 19:46.620
knowing that this was gonna be
a really difficult conversation.

19:46.620 --> 19:47.880
Mm.

19:47.880 --> 19:50.080
But then,
I thought to myself, "Hmm.

19:50.080 --> 19:53.670
Maybe if this is so hard,
am I making the wrong decision?"

19:53.670 --> 19:55.580
Uh-huh?
So I changed my mind

19:55.580 --> 19:57.750
and realized that my passion
is with advertising.

19:57.750 --> 20:00.040
Okay.
But then I had a dream.

20:00.040 --> 20:01.830
I take back the offer.

20:01.830 --> 20:03.080
Wait, no!
Dad, Dad, wait.

20:03.080 --> 20:05.000
What?

20:05.000 --> 20:06.170
I'm gonna go with you.

20:07.750 --> 20:09.250
I feel like we work
really well together,

20:09.250 --> 20:11.420
and I want to see
where this goes.

20:11.420 --> 20:13.420
Me too, son.

20:13.420 --> 20:15.830
Good.

20:15.830 --> 20:17.790
'Cause I don't think I'm ready
to step off your path just yet.

20:17.790 --> 20:19.500
Hey.

20:19.500 --> 20:23.830
It's -- It's not just
my path anymore.

20:23.830 --> 20:25.040
It's our path.

20:27.620 --> 20:30.380
If I hold my arms out
to hug you,

20:30.380 --> 20:31.460
will you let me?

20:34.670 --> 20:36.710
Only one way
to find out.

20:36.710 --> 20:40.460
♪♪

20:40.460 --> 20:41.500
Dad?

20:41.500 --> 20:42.880
Yep?

20:42.880 --> 20:44.790
This was in my dream.

20:44.790 --> 20:46.330
[ Inhales sharply ]

20:46.330 --> 20:47.290
Mine, too.

20:50.540 --> 20:53.210
[ Rare Essence's "Lock It"
plays ]
Come on!
Go-go with it!

20:53.210 --> 20:54.420
People paid money
for this?

20:54.420 --> 20:55.830
♪♪

20:55.830 --> 20:57.580
I want to throw a bottle
at Dad.

20:57.580 --> 20:59.460
This song has been on
for 45 minutes.

20:59.460 --> 21:00.830
It's been eight songs.

21:00.830 --> 21:02.580
They just all
sound the same, baby.

21:02.580 --> 21:04.120
[ Chuckles ]

21:04.120 --> 21:06.000
I'm starting
to rethink my path.

21:06.000 --> 21:07.790
Hoo. Hot mess.

21:07.790 --> 21:08.960
Let's go.

21:08.960 --> 21:10.920
Come on.

21:10.920 --> 21:12.250
Ow!

21:12.250 --> 21:13.420
Babe...

21:13.420 --> 21:15.040
Whoo!

21:15.040 --> 21:16.330
My knees ain't
what they used to be.

21:16.330 --> 21:17.330
Oh, mine either,
but keep going.

21:17.330 --> 21:18.710
Ah!

21:18.710 --> 21:19.830
I can't.

21:19.830 --> 21:21.920
Whoo!

21:21.920 --> 21:23.830
♪ What? I feel it ♪

21:23.830 --> 21:25.540
-Mom!
Shh! Daddy's working!
